instruction:
For each positive integer $k$, let $A(k)$ be the number of odd divisors of $k$ in the interval $[1, \sqrt{2k})$. Evaluate \[ \sum_{k=1}^\infty (-1)^{k-1} \frac{A(k)}{k}. \]

Options:
A. \frac{\pi^2}{8}
B. \frac{\pi^2}{12}
C. \frac{\pi^2}{32}
D. \frac{\pi^2}{20}
E. \frac{\pi^2}{24}
F. \frac{\pi^2}{16}
G. \frac{\pi^2}{28}
